<TITLE> SPPs to sell surplus power </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com)  Small power plants, like captive ones, can now sell surplus electricity to government agencies, the cabinet decided Sunday in a bid to tackle the power crisis. An advisory council meeting, chaired by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed, approved a proposal for amendment to the Small Power Plant (SPP) Policy. After the meeting the chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told reporters the decision was taken to overcome the prevailing power crisis. Until now, only captive power plants could sell electricity to the government. The proposed National Poultry Development Policy 2008 was also tabled in Sunday's cabinet meeting. The fisheries and livestock ministry has been asked to further review the draft policy before presenting a comprehensive proposal to the cabinet. The meeting approved the Medical and Dental Council (Second) Amendment Ordinance 2008. bdnews
